description: These little tarts are crispy on the outside with a delightfully creamy and moist filling.
name: Zucchini & Feta Tartlets Recipe | Woolworths
recipeIngredient: 1 medium white onion, peeled and diced
300g vegan pastry, store bought and chilled

recipeInstructions.text: Heat up a pan to a medium heat with the canola oil and fry the zucchini, onions and garlic for 6 minutes while tossing.
Roll out your chilled pastry and cut into 4 squares. Roll up the edges of the squares to create a small dip in the centre for your filling.
Transfer the fried vegetables into the centre of each pastry and cover with the feta.
Bake in the oven for 15 minutes or until the pastry is nicely browned.
Serve with chives to garnish and seasoning to taste.
